## Agent Compliance Block

> **This section is mechanically synced to all tool-specific config files (CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, etc.).**
> Edit constraints HERE in AGENTS.md, then run `scripts/sync-agent-compliance.sh` to propagate.
> Never edit the compliance block directly in CLAUDE.md or other generated files ‚Äî it will be overwritten.

### Schema Constraints (HARD ‚Äî app rejects invalid values silently)

**Roadmap item statuses:** `pending` | `up-next` | `in-progress` | `complete` | `archived`
- No other values. Not `done`, not `finished`, not `shipped`, not `blocked`.

**Project statuses:** `in-progress` | `up-next` | `pending` | `dormant` | `archived`

**When setting `status: complete`:** Always also set `completedAt: YYYY-MM-DD` (ISO date).

### Hard Rules

1. **Completion requires human sign-off.** Never set `status: complete` on a roadmap item autonomously ‚Äî including after `/build` workflows. After building, set `status: in-progress` with `nextAction: "Built ‚Äî awaiting verification"`.

2. **Never touch the running app.** No `open`, `kill`, restart. No `tauri build` without `--no-bundle`. No installing to `/Applications/`. User controls app lifecycle via in-app Update button.

3. **Priorities are unique per column.** Check existing items before assigning. Default to bottom (max + 1).

4. **Keep `nextAction` in sync.** When you create/update a spec, plan, or code ‚Äî update the roadmap item's `nextAction` field to reflect current state. Stale `nextAction` = broken UX.

5. **Document format: human-readable first.** No YAML frontmatter in spec/plan docs. Title ‚Üí one-line blockquote ‚Üí summary ‚Üí metadata below the fold.

### File Structure

```
.clawchestra/state.json       ‚Äî JSON (source of truth for roadmap, machine-readable)
CLAWCHESTRA.md                ‚Äî Human documentation (do not edit programmatically)
roadmap/{item-id}.md          ‚Äî Detail file per roadmap item
docs/specs/{item-id}-spec.md  ‚Äî Spec documents
docs/plans/{item-id}-plan.md  ‚Äî Plan documents
```

### Build & Test Commands

```bash
bun test                        # Run tests
npx tsc --noEmit                # Type check
pnpm build                      # Frontend only (fast)
npx tauri build --no-bundle     # Full release build (ALWAYS --no-bundle)
```

### Title Length Guideline
Aim for ~40 characters or fewer for roadmap item and project titles ‚Äî this fits on one line at minimum card width. Two lines is acceptable. Avoid long titles that wrap to 3+ lines.

### Roadmap Item JSON Shape

```json
{
  "id": "kebab-case-id",
  "title": "Human-readable title",
  "status": "pending",
  "priority": 1,
  "specDoc": "docs/specs/id-spec.md",
  "planDoc": "docs/plans/id-plan.md",
  "nextAction": "What happens next",
  "tags": ["bug", "feature"]
}
```

